<title>USA: Viewlogic to post Q1 charge of $4-$5 mln.</title>
<headline>Viewlogic to post Q1 charge of $4-$5 mln.</headline>
<dateline>MARLBORO, Mass. 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Viewlogic Systems Inc said Tuesday it expects to post a charge of between $4 million and $5 million in the first quarter related to its acquisition of Eagle Design Automation.</p>
<p>Viewlogic said the one-time charge primarily reflects in-process research and development costs involved with the acquisition.</p>
<p>The company, which had owned about 20 percent of Eagle, said it will be acquiring the other 80 percent for about $6.4 million in cash plus certain contingent payments tied to future sales.</p>
<p>Eagle, which is based in Beaverton, Ore., develops and markets hardware and software. The acquisition is scheduled to be complete within the next 30 days.</p>
